<br>
But anyways, I sort of agree with Demo, I wish spawn times on ubermobs would at least be reduced significantly.  Imagine if the longest you had to wait on anything to spawn was a day or two, it would be great.  Who cares how powerfull and mighty a guild could get, first off a ton of mobs require more then gear they require brains.  Second off so what?  You can kill something, go ahead, there it is.  No guild x will cockblock guild Y from killing mob Z, and if they did....so what, it'll be there again tomorrow and there's probably 2 dozen other things to kill right now.<br>
<br>
The only way real mudflation would be a problem was if everything (okay maybe just 99.9% of everything) was not No Drop.  A change like this would let more people experience more of the game, which is fun....though I guess I can see how sitting in maidens end and fungus grove for 30 hours straight each waiting for a single rare drop to finally drop for just one person (out of a hundred that need it) could be considered fun and experiencing most of the game.....wait, no I can't. <p><center><table border="1" bordercolor="#000000" 

